Privacy Policy
1. Information We Collect
We collect personal and non-personal information in various ways to provide and improve our services
Personal Information
This includes data that personally identifies you. We may collect the following
Account Information:
When you register or create an account, we collect personal details such as your name, email address, phone number, company name (if applicable), and payment information.
Event Participation Details:
Information related to your attendance at events, such as registration information, ticket purchases, preferences, and feedback.
Account Information:
When you register or create an account, we collect personal details such as your name, email address, phone number, company name (if applicable), and payment information.
Communication Information:
When you contact us through the app, email, or other communication channels, we may collect the content of your communications, including any personal details shared.
Non-Personal Information
This includes data that does not directly identify you. We may collect the following:
Usage Data:
Information about how you interact with our App or Site, including pages viewed, time spent on the platform, and features used.
Device Information:
Details about the device or browser you use to access the platform, including your IP address, operating system, browser type, and version.
Cookies and Tracking Technologies:
We may use cookies, web beacons, and similar technologies to collect information about your browsing activities to enhance user experience and analyze platform performance.
2. How We Use Your Information
We use your information for the following purposes:
To Provide and Manage Our Services
To enable account creation, ticket purchases, event registration, and participation.
To process payments and manage transactions.
To provide event-related information, updates, and notifications (e.g., schedule changes, cancellations).
â€¢ To facilitate communication between event organizers, vendors, attendees, and other users.
To improve our App and Site functionality and user experience.
To Personalize Your Experience
To tailor content, recommendations, and notifications based on your preferences, location, and activity.
To suggest relevant events or services that may interest you.
For Marketing and Promotional Purposes
To send promotional emails, newsletters, and special offers related to events, services, or features that may be of interest to you (you may opt out of these communications at any time).
To provide event organizers and vendors with insights into user behavior and preferences.
For Legal and Security Purposes
To comply with legal obligations, resolve disputes, and enforce our terms and policies.
To protect our services, platform, and users from fraud, unauthorized access, or misuse.
3. How We Share Your Information
We may share your information in the following ways:
With Event Organizers and Vendors
If you register for an event or purchase a service, we may share your information with the event organizer or vendor to facilitate event-related communication, registration, or service delivery.
Service Providers
We may share your data with third-party service providers who assist in operating the platform, processing payments, sending communications, or performing analytics. These providers are contractually obligated to protect your information.
Legal Compliance
We may disclose your personal information if required to do so by law, in response to legal process, or in connection with investigations into unlawful activities, fraud prevention, or enforcing our terms.
Business Transfers
In the event of a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets, your personal information may be transferred as part of that transaction. You will be notified if your information is transferred to another entity.
4. Your Rights and Choices
You have the following rights regarding your personal information:
Access and Update Your Information
You can access and update your account information at any time through the App or Site.
Opt-Out of Marketing Communications
You can opt out of receiving marketing emails or promotional materials by clicking the unsubscribe link provided in such emails or by contacting us directly.
Data Retention
We will retain your personal information only for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this Policy, unless a longer retention period is required or permitted by law
Delete Your Account
If you wish to delete your account and personal information, you can contact us directly, and we will process your request in accordance with applicable laws
